<h1>RSS Feeds</h1>

<p>Subscribe to nightdogs content through RSS feeds. We offer both a main feed with all posts and individual feeds for each author.</p>

<section class="feeds-section">
	<h2>Main Feed</h2>
	<div class="feed-item">
		<h3><a href="/feed/feed.xml">All Posts</a></h3>
		<p>The complete nightdogs feed with posts from all authors.</p>
		<code>/feed/feed.xml</code>
	</div>
</section>

<section class="feeds-section">
	<h2>Author Feeds</h2>
	<p>Follow your favorite authors individually:</p>

	<div class="author-feeds">
		{% for authorSlug, author in authors %}
		<div class="feed-item" data-author="{{ authorSlug }}">
			<h3><a href="/feed/{{ authorSlug }}.xml">{{ author.name }}</a></h3>
			<p>{{ author.bio | safe }}</p>
			<code>/feed/{{ authorSlug }}.xml</code>
			{% if author.note %}
			<div class="author-note">{{ author.note }}</div>
			{% endif %}
		</div>
		{% endfor %}
	</div>
</section>

<section class="feeds-section">
	<h2>How to Use RSS Feeds</h2>
	<p>RSS feeds allow you to follow nightdogs posts in your favorite RSS reader. Here are some popular options:</p>

	<ul>
		<li><strong>Web-based:</strong> Feedly, Inoreader, NewsBlur</li>
		<li><strong>Desktop:</strong> NetNewsWire (Mac), Thunderbird (cross-platform)</li>
		<li><strong>Mobile:</strong> Reeder (iOS), gReader (Android)</li>
	</ul>

	<p>Simply copy the feed URL and add it to your RSS reader to start receiving updates.</p>
</section>

